<P><H1 align=center>DC222 – LEASEHOLD DETAILS</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red>Areas shown in red are mandatory and 
must be completed to proceed.</FONT>           </P>
<P>Information captured on this screen may need to be provided by the 
applicant’s solicitors if not known by the applicant(s).</P>
<P><H3>Leasehold details: </H3>This button will only be 
highlighted if the tenure of the property is Leasehold. Clicking this button 
brings up a box with the following fields:
<P></P>
<P><H3>Original term of lease: </H3>Input the original term of 
the lease on the property to be mortgaged.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Unexpired term of lease: </H3>Input the number of years 
remaining on the lease at the time of application, information to be provided by 
the applicant or their solicitors.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Annual ground rent: </H3>Input the total amount of 
ground rent payable to the freeholder as part of the lease agreement. May or may 
not be currently payable.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Date lease started: </H3>Input the commencement date of 
the lease. Applicant or solicitors will have this information.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Can ground rent be increased: </H3>Is the ground rent 
specified in the lease fixed, or is there scope for this to be increased by the 
freeholder. Input any details you have of the ground rent agreement in the box 
provided.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Annual service charges: </H3>These are charges payable 
to the freeholder for maintenance and servicing of the property. Should any be 
payable, they will be detailed in the lease agreement.
<P></P>
